Show HN: Pageblox – React SDK for reviewing UX/UI changes in deployments
text:
Hi HN community!

I've been working on it for the last couple of months and looking to get some people to try it out and give feedback. If you're interested, please sign up through the 'Get Beta Access' button.

As a front-end engineer that's worked in remote/hybrid teams, I noticed a pain point during the product review process. Front-end features had to get reviewed by PMs/Designers/QA, and it took a lot of back-and-forths while juggling various tools.

This led to release delays to production, uncaught bugs, and poor documentation.

With Pageblox, these reviews can take place directly in the app in a collaborative space, creating a much faster feedback loop.

Here are the instructions to try it out yourself on the site:

1. Create an account here: https://www.pageblox.io/register. 2. Open a new tab, go to https://www.pageblox.io, then click the 'Try Now' button (must be on desktop). 3. Double-click on the screen to start commenting!

Thanks for reading!
